II. SCREW OPERATOR
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

DNA is generated by repeated applications of a single operator.

σ = S(θ,h)

where

S(θ,h) = Rz(θ) · Tz(h)

Rz(θ) = rotation about z-axis
Tz(h) = translation along z-axis

Iteration

xₙ₊₁ = S(θ,h)xₙ

or

gₙ = g₀σⁿ

This is a discrete subgroup of SE(3).




